File: Lesotho police allege Maesaiah Thabane (pictured) hired eight assassins to kill her husband Thomas Thabane's former wife Lipolelo Thabane. JOHANNESBURG - Lesotho's Prime Minister, Thomas Thabane has skipped the country. He was due in court in connection with his estranged wife's murder. Thabane faces charges of murder and attempted murder. READ: Lesotho PM to be charged with murdering wife His estranged wife was shot several times in her car near her home. Thabane remarried two months after her death. His second wife, Maesaiah, was charged with her murder after briefly fleeing the country.